HEADWORD: Primus
<hw>Pri"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the
first.]</ety> <def>One of the bishops of the Episcopal Church of
Scotland, who presides at the meetings of the bishops, and has certain
privileges but no metropolitan authority.</def> <rj><au>Internat.
Cyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

